 "executive_summary": "This study examined the MART-1-specific TCR DMF5 bound to cognate peptide\u2013MHC-I complexes to address a critical challenge in TCR-based immunotherapy: cross-reactivity toward off-target peptides. The authors demonstrated that affinity-enhancing mutations paradoxically increase cross-recognition of structurally similar peptides, and developed a structure-guided design approach to improve specificity independent of binding affinity. Applied to DMF5, this method reduced cross-reactivity against MART-1 homologs and eliminated recognition of divergent, unrelated epitopes. This work matters for TCR engineering because off-target cross-reactivity can cause immune toxicity in therapeutic applications; the structure-guided strategy offers a rational path to develop more specific TCR therapeutics without the unintended consequences of traditional affinity maturation.",
